{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/910863.Spin", "title": "Spin", "titleComplete": "Spin (Spin, #1)", "description": "Spin is Robert Charles Wilson's Hugo Award-winning masterpiece\u2015a stunning combination of a galactic \"what if\" and a small-scale, very human story. One night in October when he was ten years old, Tyler Dupree stood in his backyard and watched the stars go out. They all flared into brilliance at once, then disappeared, replaced by a flat, empty black barrier. He and his best friends, Jason and Diane Lawton, had seen what became known as the Big Blackout. It would shape their lives. The effect is worldwide. The sun is now a featureless disk\u2015a heat source, rather than an astronomical object. The moon is gone, but tides remain. Not only have the world's artificial satellites fallen out of orbit, their recovered remains are pitted and aged, as though they'd been in space far longer than their known lifespans. As Tyler, Jason, and Diane grow up, a space probe reveals a bizarre truth: The barrier is artificial, generated by huge alien artifacts. Time is passing faster outside the barrier than inside\u2015more than a hundred million years per year on Earth. At this rate, the death throes of the sun are only about forty years in our future. Jason, now a promising young scientist, devotes his life to working against this slow-moving apocalypse. Diane throws herself into hedonism, marrying a sinister cult leader who's forged a new religion out of the fears of the masses. Earth sends terraforming machines to Mars to let the onrush of time do its work, turning the planet green. Next they send humans\u2026 and immediately get back an emissary with thousands of years of stories to tell about the settling of Mars. Then Earth's probes reveal that an identical barrier has appeared around Mars. Jason, desperate, seeds near space with self-replicating machines that will scatter copies of themselves outward from the sun\u2015and report back on what they find. Life on Earth is about to get much, much stranger.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1406383726i/910863.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction Fantasy", "Speculative Fiction", "Hugo Awards", "Fiction", "Space", "Fantasy", "Time Travel", "Dystopia", "Aliens", "Science Fiction"], "asin": "076534825X", "isbn": "076534825X", "isbn13": "9780765348258", "publisher": "Tor Science Fiction", "series": ["Spin"], "author": ["Robert Charles Wilson"], "publishDate": 1139299200000, "characters": ["Jason Lawton", "Tyler Dupree", "E.D. Lawton", "Diane Lawton"], "ratingHistogram": [522, 1716, 7829, 16881, 14078], "ratingsCount": 41026, "reviewsCount": 2730, "numPages": 458, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Hugo Award", "awardedAt": 1136102400000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 1136102400000, "category": "Best SF Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Kurd-La\u00dfwitz-Preis", "awardedAt": 1167638400000, "category": "Bestes ausl\u00e4ndisches Werk (Best Foreign Work)", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Sunburst Award", "awardedAt": 1136102400000, "category": "Canadian Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "John W. Campbell Memorial Award", "awardedAt": 1136102400000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Grand Prix de l'Imaginaire", "awardedAt": 1199174400000, "category": "Roman \u00e9tranger", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Premio Ignotus", "awardedAt": 1230796800000, "category": "Mejor novela extranjera (Best Foreign Novel)", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Prix Aurora Award", "awardedAt": 1136102400000, "category": "Best Long-Form Work in English", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "SF ga Yomitai", "awardedAt": 1199174400000, "category": "Best Translated SF of the Year in Japan", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Seiun Award \u661f\u96f2\u8cde", "awardedAt": 1230796800000, "category": "Best Translated Long Story", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/76683.Foundation_s_Edge", "title": "Foundation's Edge", "titleComplete": "Foundation's Edge (Foundation, #4)", "description": "At last, the costly and bitter war between the two Foundations had come to an end. The scientists of the First Foundation had proved victorious; and now they return to Hari Seldon's long-established plan to build a new Empire on the ruins of the old. But rumors persist that the Second Foundation is not destroyed after all\u2014and that its still-defiant survivors are preparing their revenge. Now two exiled citizens of the Foundation\u2014a renegade Councilman and a doddering historian\u2014set out in search of the mythical planet Earth. . .and proof that the Second Foundation still exists.Meanwhile someone\u2014or something\u2014outside of both Foundations seems to be orchestrating events to suit its own ominous purpose. Soon representatives of both the First and Second Foundations will find themselves racing toward a mysterious world called Gaia and a final shocking destiny at the very end of the universe!", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1442311409i/76683.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction Fantasy", "Novels", "Hugo Awards", "Fiction", "Space", "Classics", "Space Opera", "Fantasy", "Audiobook", "Science Fiction"], "asin": "0553293389", "isbn": "0553293389", "isbn13": "9780553293388", "publisher": "Bantam/Spectra", "series": ["Greater Foundation Universe", "Foundation (Publication Order)", "Foundation (Chronological Order)"], "author": ["Isaac Asimov"], "publishDate": 1293782400000, "characters": ["Janov Pelorat", "Golan Trevize", "Blissenobiarella"], "ratingHistogram": [443, 2380, 15056, 34568, 36531], "ratingsCount": 88978, "reviewsCount": 2170, "numPages": 450, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Hugo Award", "awardedAt": 410256000000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Nebula Award", "awardedAt": 37872