{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/218709.The_Wanderer", "title": "The Wanderer", "titleComplete": "The Wanderer", "description": "All eyes were watching the eclipse of the Moon when the Wanderer--a huge, garishly colored artificial world--emerged. Only a few scientists even suspected its presence, and then, suddenly and silently, it arrived, dwarfing and threatening the Moon and wreaking havoc on Earth's tides and weather. Though the Wanderer is stopping in the solar system only to refuel, its mere presence is catastrophic. A tense, thrilling, and towering achievement. Winner of the Hugo Award for Best SF Novel of the Year! All eyes were watching the eclipse of the Moon when the Wanderer--a huge, garishly colored artificial world--emerged. Only a few scientists even suspected its presence, and then, suddenly and silently, it arrived, dwarfing and threatening the Moon and wreaking havoc on Earth's tides and weather. Though the Wanderer is stopping in the solar system only to refuel, its mere presence is catastrophic. A tense, thrilling, and towering achievement. Winner of the Hugo Award for Best SF Novel of the Year!", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1387707752i/218709.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction Fantasy", "Speculative Fiction", "Novels", "Apocalyptic", "Hugo Awards", "Fiction", "Fantasy", "Classics", "Post Apocalyptic", "Science Fiction"], "asin": "0575071125", "isbn": "0575071125", "isbn13": "9780575071124", "publisher": "Victor Gollancz", "author": ["Fritz Leiber"], "publishDate": 978336000000, "characters": ["Paul Hagbolt", "Margo Gelhorn"], "ratingHistogram": [173, 438, 984, 944, 527], "ratingsCount": 3066, "reviewsCount": 224, "numPages": 346, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Hugo Award", "awardedAt": -157737600000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/643792.Slan", "title": "Slan", "titleComplete": "Slan (Slan, #1)", "description": "In the 1940s, the Golden Age of science fiction flowered in the magazine Astounding. Editor John W. Campbell, Jr., discovered and promoted great new writers such as A.E. van Vogt, whose novel Slan was one of the works of the era.Slan is the story of Jommy Cross, the orphan mutant outcast from a future society prejudiced against mutants, or slans. Throughout the forties and into the fifties, Slan was considered the single most important SF novel, the one great book that everyone had to read. Today it remains a monument to pulp SF adventure, filled with constant action and a cornucopia of ideas.This edition has a new introduction by Kevin J. Anderson.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388290996i/643792.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction Fantasy", "Speculative Fiction", "Novels", "Hugo Awards", "Fiction", "Classics", "Dystopia", "Space Opera", "Fantasy", "Science Fiction"], "asin": "0312852363", "isbn": "0312852363", "isbn13": "9780312852368", "publisher": "Orb Books", "series": ["Slan"], "author": ["Kevin J. Anderson", "A.E. van Vogt"], "publishDate": 887529600000, "characters": ["Jommy Cross"], "ratingHistogram": [110, 513, 1655, 1858, 1303], "ratingsCount": 5439, "reviewsCount": 451, "numPages": 272, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Analog Award", "awardedAt": -568051200000, "category": "All-Time Best Book", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Retro Hugo Award", "awardedAt": 1451635200000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/102281.The_Big_Time", "title": "The Big Time", "titleComplete": "The Big Time", "description": "Have you ever worried about your memory, because it doesn't seem to recall exactly the same past from one day to the next? Have you ever thought that the whole universe might be a crazy, mixed-up dream? If you have, then you've had hints of the Change War.It's been going on for a billion years and it will last another billion or so. Up and down the timeline, the two sides--\"Spiders\" and \"Snakes\"--battle endlessly to change the future and the past. Our lives, our memories, are their battleground. And in the midst of the war is the Place, outside space and time, where Greta Forzane and the other Entertainers provide solace and r-&amp;-r for tired time warriors.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1312007868i/102281.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction Fantasy", "Mystery", "Speculative Fiction", "Novels", "Hugo Awards", "Fiction", "Classics", "Time Travel", "Fantasy", "Science Fiction"], "asin": "0312890788", "isbn": "0312890788", "isbn13": "9780312890780", "publisher": "Orb Books", "series": ["Change War"], "author": ["Fritz Leiber"], "publishDate": 983952000000, "ratingHistogram": [304, 732, 1371, 1091, 601], "ratingsCount": 4099, "reviewsCount": 438, "numPages": 128, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Hugo Award", "awardedAt": -378662400000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "British Science Fiction Association Award", "awardedAt": 1167638400000, "category": "50th Anniversary Award Best Novel of 1958", "hasWon": null}]}
