{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/175324.Double_Star", "title": "Double Star", "titleComplete": "Double Star", "description": "One minute, down and out actor Lorenzo Smythe was \u2014 as usual \u2014 in a bar, drinking away his troubles as he watched his career go down the tubes. Then a space pilot bought him a drink, and the next thing Smythe knew, he was shanghaied to Mars.Suddenly he found himself agreeing to the most difficult role of his career: impersonating an important politician who had been kidnapped. Peace with the Martians was at stake \u2014 failure to pull off the act could result in interplanetary war. And Smythe's own life was on the line \u2014 for if he wasn't assassinated, there was always the possibility that he might be trapped in his new role forever!", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327984434i/175324.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction Fantasy", "Speculative Fiction", "Novels", "Hugo Awards", "Fiction", "Classics", "Politics", "Fantasy", "Audiobook", "Science Fiction"], "asin": "0345330137", "isbn": "0345330137", "isbn13": "9780345330130", "publisher": "Del Rey", "author": ["Robert A. Heinlein"], "publishDate": 529484400000, "characters": ["Lorenzo Smythe"], "ratingHistogram": [227, 1089, 6029, 8796, 6823], "ratingsCount": 22964, "reviewsCount": 967, "numPages": 243, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Hugo Award", "awardedAt": -441820800000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 536486400000, "category": "All-Time Best SF Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16703.The_Yiddish_Policemen_s_Union", "title": "The Yiddish Policemen's Union", "titleComplete": "The Yiddish Policemen's Union", "description": "For sixty years, Jewish refugees and their descendants have prospered in the Federal District of Sitka, a \"temporary\" safe haven created in the wake of revelations of the Holocaust and the shocking 1948 collapse of the fledgling state of Israel. Proud, grateful, and longing to be American, the Jews of the Sitka District have created their own little world in the Alaskan panhandle, a vibrant, gritty, soulful, and complex frontier city that moves to the music of Yiddish. For sixty years they have been left alone, neglected and half-forgotten in a backwater of history. Now the District is set to revert to Alaskan control, and their dream is coming to an end: once again the tides of history threaten to sweep them up and carry them off into the unknown. But homicide detective Meyer Landsman of the District Police has enough problems without worrying about the upcoming Reversion. His life is a shambles, his marriage a wreck, his career a disaster. He and his half-Tlingit partner, Berko Shemets, can't catch a break in any of their outstanding cases. Landsman's new supervisor is the love of his life\u2014and also his worst nightmare. And in the cheap hotel where he has washed up, someone has just committed a murder\u2014right under Landsman's nose. Out of habit, obligation, and a mysterious sense that it somehow offers him a shot at redeeming himself, Landsman begins to investigate the killing of his neighbor, a former chess prodigy. But when word comes down from on high that the case is to be dropped immediately, Landsman soon finds himself contending with all the powerful forces of faith, obsession, hopefulness, evil, and salvation that are his heritage\u2014and with the unfinished business of his marriage to Bina Gelbfish, the one person who understands his darkest fears. At once a gripping whodunit, a love story, an homage to 1940s noir, and an exploration of the mysteries of exile and redemption, The Yiddish Policemen's Union is a novel only Michael Chabon could have written.(front flap)", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1528196883i/16703.jpg", "genres": ["Alternate History", "Mystery", "Literature", "Jewish", "Novels", "Crime", "Fiction", "Fantasy", "Literary Fiction", "Science Fiction"], "asin": "0007149824", "isbn": "0007149824", "isbn13": "9780007149827", "publisher": "HarperCollins", "author": ["Michael Chabon"], "publishDate": 1178002800000, "characters": ["Mendel Shpilman", "Ester-Malke Shemets", "Berko Shemets", "Itzik Zimbalist", "Meyer Landsman", "Naomi Landsman", "Alter Litvak", "Bina Gelbfish", "Hertz Shemets"], "places": ["Sitka, Alaska"], "ratingHistogram": [2646, 6187, 19681, 29960, 18029], "ratingsCount": 76503, "reviewsCount": 7687, "numPages": 414, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Hugo Award", "awardedAt": 1199174400000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Nebula Award", "awardedAt": 1167638400000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 1199174400000, "category": "Best Science Fiction Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Hammett Prize", "awardedAt": 1167638400000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "California Book Award", "awardedAt": 1167638400000, "category": "Fiction (Gold)", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "John W. Campbell Memorial Award", "awardedAt": 1199174400000, "category": "Best Science Fiction Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Edgar Award", "awardedAt": 1199174400000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Premio Ignotus", "awardedAt": 1230796800000, "category": "Mejor Novela Extranjera", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Sidewise Award", "awardedAt": 1167638400000, "category": "Long Form", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Seiun Award \u661f\u96f2\u8cde", "awardedAt": 12623