{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/77505.Green_Mars", "title": "Green Mars", "titleComplete": "Green Mars (Mars Trilogy, #2)", "description": "In the Nebula Award winning Red Mars, Kim Stanley Robinson began his critically acclaimed epic saga of the colonization of Mars, Now the Hugo Award winning Green Mars continues the thrilling and timeless tale of humanity's struggle to survive at its farthest frontier.Nearly a generation has passed since the first pioneers landed, but the transformation of Mars to an Earthlike planet has just begun. The plan is opposed by those determined to preserve the planet's hostile, barren beauty. Led by rebels like Peter Clayborne, these young people are the first generation of children born on Mars. They will be joined by original settlers Maya Toitovna, Simon Frasier, and Sax Russell. Against this cosmic backdrop, passions, rivalries, and friendships explode in a story as spectacular as the planet itself.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1389628152i/77505.jpg", "genres": ["Hard Science Fiction", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Speculative Fiction", "Novels", "Hugo Awards", "Fiction", "Space", "Fantasy", "Space Opera", "Science Fiction"], "asin": "0553572393", "isbn": "0553572393", "isbn13": "9780553572391", "publisher": "Spectra Books", "series": ["Mars Trilogy"], "author": ["Kim Stanley Robinson"], "publishDate": 736239600000, "characters": ["Arthur Randolph", "Peter Clayborne", "Maya Toitovna", "Simon Frasier", "Sax Russell", "Hiroko Ai"], "places": ["Mars"], "ratingHistogram": [624, 2048, 8361, 14619, 12448], "ratingsCount": 38100, "reviewsCount": 1306, "numPages": 624, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Hugo Award", "awardedAt": 757411200000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Nebula Award", "awardedAt": 757411200000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 757411200000, "category": "Best Sci