{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/77773.To_Say_Nothing_of_the_Dog", "title": "To Say Nothing of the Dog", "titleComplete": "To Say Nothing of the Dog (Oxford Time Travel, #2)", "description": "Connie Willis' Hugo and Nebula Award-winning Doomsday Book uses time travel for a serious look at how people connect with each other. In this Hugo-winning companion to that novel, she offers a completely different kind of time travel adventure: a delightful romantic comedy that pays hilarious homage to Jerome K. Jerome's Three Men in a Boat.When too many jumps back to 1940 leave 21st century Oxford history student Ned Henry exhausted, a relaxing trip to Victorian England seems the perfect solution. But complexities like recalcitrant rowboats, missing cats, and love at first sight make Ned's holiday anything but restful - to say nothing of the way hideous pieces of Victorian art can jeopardize the entire course of history.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1469410460i/77773.jpg", "genres": ["Humor", "Historical Fiction", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Mystery", "Historical", "Fiction", "Romance", "Fantasy", "Time Travel", "Science Fiction"], "asin": "0553575384", "isbn": "0553575384", "isbn13": "9780553575385", "publisher": "Bantam Books", "series": ["Oxford Time Travel"], "author": ["Connie Willis"], "publishDate": 912499200000, "characters": ["Ned Henry", "Verity Kindle"], "places": ["River Thames, England", "Oxford, Oxfordshire, England", "Coventry, Warwickshire, England", "Coventry Cathedral, Coventry, England", "Oxford University, Oxford, England"], "ratingHistogram": [776, 1712, 6460, 15068, 16552], "ratingsCount": 40568, "reviewsCount": 4758, "numPages": 512, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Hugo Award", "awardedAt": 915177600000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Nebula Award", "awardedAt": 883641600000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Locus Awar