{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/14201.Jonathan_Strange_Mr_Norrell", "title": "Jonathan Strange & Mr. Norrell", "titleComplete": "Jonathan Strange & Mr. Norrell", "description": "The year is 1806. England is beleaguered by the long war with Napoleon, and centuries have passed since practical magicians faded into the nation's past. But scholars of this glorious history discover that one remains: the reclusive Mr Norrell, whose displays of magic send a thrill through the country. Proceeding to London, he raises a beautiful woman from the dead and summons an army of ghostly ships to terrify the French. Yet the cautious, fussy Norrell is challenged by the emergence of another magician: the brilliant novice Jonathan Strange. Young, handsome and daring, Strange is the very antithesis of Norrell. So begins a dangerous battle between these two great men which overwhelms that between England and France. And their own obsessions and secret dabblings with the dark arts are going to cause more trouble than they can imagine.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1357027589i/14201.jpg", "genres": ["Alternate History", "Historical Fiction", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Magic", "Historical", "Fiction", "Adult", "Fantasy", "Magical Realism", "Audiobook"], "publisher": "Tor Books", "series": ["Strange & Norrell"], "author": ["Susanna Clarke"], "publishDate": 1154415600000, "characters": ["Mrs Delgado", "George Gordon Byron, 6th Baron Byron", "Arabella Strange", "Henry Woodhope", "Lady Emma Pole", "Mr. Honeyfoot", "Sir Walter Pole", "Vinculus", "John Segundus", "Stephen Black", "Henry Lascelles", "Gilbert Norrell", "Jonathan Strange", "Arthur Wellesley, 1st Duke of Wellington", "Louisa Greysteel", "Flora Greysteel", "Christopher Drawlight", "John Uskglass (The Raven King)", "The Gentleman with the Thistledown Hair", "Dr. Lancelot Greysteel", "John Childermass"], "places": ["London, England", "England", "United K